Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.98,0:32:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I give thanks to Thee
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.20,0:32:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have been assigned
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.23,0:32:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this mission
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.93,0:32:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by which I may serve Thee
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.73,0:33:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and my fellow men.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.78,0:33:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.08,0:33:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,이러한 것에 대한 이해는
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.84,0:33:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,애고를 강화시키는 것 대신
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.78,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,겸손함을 강화시키고
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,제가 당신의 가르침을
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.63,0:33:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,제 동료 인간에게
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.86,0:33:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,전달할 수 있게 되신 것에 대해서
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.32,0:33:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,신에게 감사를 드리게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.06,0:33:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.58,0:33:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So then,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.45,0:33:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.48,0:33:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the teacher becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.42,0:33:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned with serving
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.51,0:33:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,God and his fellow man
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.85,0:33:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,serving others
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.85,0:33:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.96,0:33:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what he has become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.22,0:33:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.98,0:33:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,자신이 된 그것으로서
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.98,0:33:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,신과 동료 인간과
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.93,0:33:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,정렬되게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.75,0:33:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,가르침으로서 정렬시켜줍니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.13,0:33:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.65,0:33:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.30,0:33:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.03,0:33:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't read anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.85,0:33:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, non-binding.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.98,0:33:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when I was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.79,0:33:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was invited to become
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.31,0:33:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of a certain group
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.74,0:33:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I found out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.70,0:34:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that you had to take an oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.81,0:34:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,제가 어릴 때
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.64,0:34:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,어떤 사람들과 어울리기 위해서
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.66,0:34:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,그들 외에 멤버가 되기 위해서는
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.16,0:34:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,어떤 선서를 해야 된다는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.21,0:34:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,알게 되었습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.00,0:34:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, at age 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.09,0:34:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I was 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.07,0:34:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,열두 살 때였는데요.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.07,0:34:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew better than to take an oath.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.21,0:34:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,저는 그 선서를 해서는
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.76,0:34:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,안 된다는 것을 알았습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.07,0:34:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.40,0:34:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can discuss,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.96,0:34:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I can reveal this result.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.28,0:34:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,이것에 대해서
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.88,0:34:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.61,0:34:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.78,0:34:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.15,0:34:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because oaths are binding
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.44,0:34:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,from one lifetime to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.90,0:34:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 선서를 하지 않아야 하는 것은
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.32,0:34:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,선서는 생을 거듭해서
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.07,0:34:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,그 사람을 묶기 때문입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.34,0:34:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So a true teacher wants you to be free
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and not bound.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.63,0:34:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,진정한 스승은 당신이
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.69,0:34:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,자유롭기를 원하지
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.61,0:34:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,묶이기를 원하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.11,0:34:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.86,0:34:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,students are free to come and go
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.90,0:35:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,without trying to persuade them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.92,0:35:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,coerce them, threaten them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.30,0:35:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,intimidate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.78,0:35:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,excommunicate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.15,0:35:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,tax them,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.36,0:35:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or chop their heads off.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.13,0:35:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.80,0:35:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,스승은 학생들이 자유롭게 오가길 원합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.42,0:35:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,설득하지도 않고,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.53,0:35:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,강제력을 행사하지도 않고,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.92,0:35:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,겁을 주지도 않고,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.30,0:35:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,세금을 매기지도 않고,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.28,0:35:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,머리를 잘라버리지도 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.67,0:35:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who make converts
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.88,0:35:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving you your choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.84,0:35:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to either join them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.69,0:35:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or become beheaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.61,0:35:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,그 스승을 따르게 되는 사람 중에는
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.46,0:35:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,여기 들어오든지,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.44,0:35:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,아니면 머리가 잘리든지의 선택권에서
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.53,0:35:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇게 결정한 사람들도 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.17,0:35:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, real integrity allows for freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.13,0:35:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to say yes or no
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.32,0:35:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,without any consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.59,0:35:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if a person declines,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.11,0:35:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,then the proper thing for the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.98,0:36:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is to pray for that person's enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.51,0:36:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 진정한 스승은 자유를 허락하고
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.73,0:36:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,그에게 yes나 no를 선택할 기회를 주고
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.13,0:36:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,그들이 만약 거부한다면
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.42,0:36:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,그들을 위해서
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.57,0:36:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,그들이 알만한 적당한 길을 선택하도록 기도해 줍니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.80,0:36:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.98,0:36:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the teacher is inspirational.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.86,0:36:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth avoids glamorization, seduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.53,0:36:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and theatrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.09,0:36:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 영감을 고치시키고
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.44,0:36:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,어떤 유혹하는 것이나
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.76,0:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,그 다음에 어떤 과시하는 것
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.88,0:36:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,이런 것을 모두 피합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.63,0:36:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is devoid of neediness of worldly wealth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.50,0:36:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,prestige, titles, pomp, edifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.88,0:36:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 세상적인 부와
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.76,0:37:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,명성과 어떤 거대한 구조물
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.86,0:37:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,이런 것들을 모두 필요로 하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.55,0:37:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.92,0:37:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth stands on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.21,0:37:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 그 자체로 섭니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.03,0:37:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without formalities, theatrics, drum and bugle,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.53,0:37:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,orchestras, and dancing girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.23,0:37:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 어떤 과대 포장이라든지
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.67,0:37:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,오케스트라 뮤직이라든지
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.13,0:37:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,아니면 춤추는 여인들 없이도
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.17,0:37:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,스스로 그 자체로서 섭니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.98,0:37:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think in its higher form
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.01,0:37:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it also avoids extremes of asceticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.00,0:37:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,그리고 또 한 가지는
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.82,0:37:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,어떤 극단주의적인 금욕주의도 거부합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.38,0:37:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that occurs in the Hindu tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.98,0:37:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,그것은
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.67,0:37:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.57,0:37:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Asceticism to an extreme degree
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.13,0:37:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're profoundly emaciated
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.38,0:37:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and falling over from hunger and weakness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.40,0:37:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.86,0:37:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.13,0:38:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,힌두 전통에서 발생한
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.48,0:38:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,아주 극단주의적인 어떤 금욕주의
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.96,0:38:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,배고픔으로 인해서 바짝 말라서 쓰러지는
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.15,0:38:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,그러한 것은 결코 필요하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.05,0:38:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth itself fulfilling and complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.84,0:38:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is already total and complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.30,0:38:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Has no need to proselytize,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.46,0:38:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,gain adherence, sign up members, followers,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.67,0:38:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,send in dues.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.80,0:38:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 자기 전통에서
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.67,0:38:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,충족적이며
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.61,0:38:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,이미 완전하고
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.88,0:38:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,완전 무결하기 때문에
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.82,0:38:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,전도할 필요도 없고
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.26,0:38:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,추종자들을 얻으려고 노력하거나
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.71,0:38:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,멤버들을 이렇게
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.15,0:38:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,사인업 시키지도 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.59,0:38:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.07,0:38:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.32,0:38:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,there is non-involvement in worldly affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.09,0:38:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.28,0:38:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but not of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.01,0:39:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.57,0:39:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in the world but not of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.78,0:39:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,세상에 있기지만 세상적이지는 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.32,0:39:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.23,0:39:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.80,0:39:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,있는 그대로 있을 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.65,0:39:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no need to control others.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.55,0:39:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how much of the conflicts of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.46,0:39:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are due to one group or person trying to control others.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.59,0:39:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If I think this way, you have to think this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.92,0:39:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeking agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.15,0:39:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does the world seek agreement?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.61,0:39:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.28,0:39:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,세상에 많은 문제는
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.71,0:39:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,누군가를 통제하려고 하는 것 때문에 일어납니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.28,0:39:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,모두 자신이 하고자 하는 것에
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.65,0:39:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,동의를 구하려고 하기 때문에
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.32,0:39:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,이러한 폭력들이 발생합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.30,0:39:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to think the way they think.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.69,0:40:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it people insist that you think the way they must think?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.57,0:40:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,우리는 상대방이 생각하는 대로 생각하도록 강요받습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.19,0:40:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,왜 우리가 그래야 할까요?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.73,0:40:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so you can believe in Christmas or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.19,0:40:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,당신은 크리스마스를 믿어도 되고 믿지 않아도 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.07,0:40:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I believe in Christmas, you don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.07,0:40:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,제가 크리스마스를 믿는다고 해서 당신이 꼭 그래야 할 필요는 없습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.86,0:40:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.19,0:40:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't believe in Christmas, you don't have to stop believing in Christmas
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.42,0:40:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because I don't believe in Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.13,0:40:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,제가 크리스마스를 믿지 않는다고 해서
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.86,0:40:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,당신이 크리스마스를 믿는 것을 그만둬야 할 필요도 없습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.30,0:40:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.61,0:40:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The daily news is when you see it goes back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.48,0:40:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for these groups trying to force other people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.88,0:40:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to think and see and perceive the way they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.88,0:40:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 이러한 것을 이해하게 되면
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.67,0:40:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,우리가 매일 신문에서 보는 것처럼
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.01,0:40:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,다른 사람이 자기가 생각하는 대로
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.34,0:40:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,자신이 지각하는 대로
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.90,0:40:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,자신이 믿는 대로 다른 사람들에게 강요하는 것이
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.96,0:40:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,얼마나 우습다는 것을 알 수 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.21,0:41:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you say, why is the human that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.80,0:41:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That he wants everybody to agree with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.01,0:41:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.67,0:41:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,인간은 다른 사람들이 자신과 똑같이
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.75,0:41:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,생각하고 행동하기를 원하는 것일까요?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.13,0:41:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must everybody agree with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.86,0:41:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,왜 모든 사람이 당신에게 동의해야 합니까?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.76,0:41:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of that which is anti-God
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.55,0:41:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and anti-freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.90,0:41:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.25,0:41:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,신에게 부정적인 것의 핵심은
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.71,0:41:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,자기애적인 애고의 애고입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.90,0:41:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.78,0:41:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to see it my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.55,0:41:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,모든 사람들이 내가 보는 것처럼 봐야 되죠.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.50,0:41:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I am right and you are wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.61,0:41:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 내가 옳고 당신은 그르기 때문입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.92,0:41:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's egotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.63,0:41:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,이러한 것이 바로 자기중심주의입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.71,0:41:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the opposite of God, the enemy of God
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.69,0:42:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.65,0:42:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에 신에게 반대하는 것
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.42,0:42:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,그리고 신에게 반대하는 것이
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.28,0:42:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,신에게 대항하는 것은
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.53,0:42:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,자기애적인 애고의 핵심입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.32,0:42:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of the ego is me, me, me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.94,0:42:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 애고의 핵심은
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.73,0:42:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,나, 나, 나를 찾는 바로 그것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.92,0:42:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.15,0:42:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.75,0:42:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.30,0:42:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Photograph me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.76,0:42:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Worship me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.92,0:42:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Send your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.05,0:42:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Send your emails.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.32,0:42:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Send your...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.88,0:42:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That machine that they talk on.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.76,0:42:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.71,0:42:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Send me your blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.78,0:42:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,블로그도 좀 보내주시고.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.32,0:42:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is suffocating with blogism.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.40,0:42:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,세상은 지금 블로그리즘에 의해서 아주 숨막힐 지경입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.55,0:42:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So all that people do when they make an utterance
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.13,0:42:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is a verbalized blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.26,0:43:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 어떤 사람이 무언가를 얘기할 때
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.11,0:43:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean blog?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.38,0:43:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,블로그.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.01,0:43:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.38,0:43:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.65,0:43:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,사람들이 말할 때 블로그리즘.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.50,0:43:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,블로그리즘.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.21,0:43:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,우리가 블로그로 하는 그런 것들이 언어와되고 있는 것이나 마찬가지입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.53,0:43:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you boil it down,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.50,0:43:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there's only God and blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.86,0:43:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 이것을 바닥까지 들여다보게 되면
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.40,0:43:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,신과 블로그만 남게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.46,0:43:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, God doesn't know how to work a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.61,0:43:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,그런데 신은 컴퓨터를 사용할지 모릅니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.13,0:43:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.96,0:43:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.03,0:43:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.11,0:43:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.17,0:43:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.21,0:43:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.23,0:43:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.28,0:43:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.30,0:43:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.36,0:43:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.40,0:43:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.46,0:43:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know how to text.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.34,0:43:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,문자를 보낼 수 있는 능력이 없습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.44,0:44:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So you break the world, the tragedies of the world down,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.05,0:44:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see them as humor and absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.76,0:44:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,세상의 문제들을 이렇게 차근차근 나열해 보게 되면
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.30,0:44:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,거기서 휴머를 보게 되고 이것이 부조리하다는 것을 알게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.84,0:44:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So then there is only knowing the truth and ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.44,0:44:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에 결국에는
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.53,0:44:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,진실을 아는 것과 무지만이 남게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.65,0:44:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jesus Christ said that there is only one source of sin
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.46,0:44:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is only one sin and that is of ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.11,0:44:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 예수님께서는 죄의 근원은 단 하나이고
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.44,0:44:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,그것은 무지라고 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.19,0:44:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There is only ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.01,0:44:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,오로지 무지만이 있을 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.13,0:44:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which we consider evil and all that is all profound ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.09,0:45:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 우리가 악마라고 여기는 그러한 것들은
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.36,0:45:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,사실은 아주 심온한 무지일 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.84,0:45:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.13,0:45:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,부처님도 같은 말씀을 하셨습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.73,0:45:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Krishna said the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.30,0:45:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I say the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.90,0:45:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,박사님도 같은 말씀을 하셨습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.00,0:45:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them out there are just plain stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.71,0:45:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,세상에 많은 사람들은 그냥 어리석은 짓을 하고 있을 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.25,0:45:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The karmically earn the right to hear the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.59,0:45:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and be exposed to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.44,0:45:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,just as one karmically evolves to the place
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.75,0:45:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can comprehend the truth and recognize the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.32,0:46:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,진실을 배우고 진실에 노출되기 위해서
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.53,0:46:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,사람은 카르마적으로 그것을 획득해야 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.55,0:46:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha said many can listen but few can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.92,0:46:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 부처님은 많은 사람들이 진실을
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.34,0:46:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수는 있지만 진정으로
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.30,0:46:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,들은 사람들은 적다고 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.09,0:46:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Many listen but few can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.07,0:46:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,많은 사람들이 들을 수는 있으나
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.03,0:46:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,아주 소수만이 이해할 수 있다고 했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.46,0:46:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha spoke to those who are able to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.21,0:46:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,To those who can hear, he spoke the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.86,0:46:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha spoke to those who can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.78,0:46:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,부처님은 들을 수 있는 사람들은
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.94,0:46:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,이해할 수 있는 사람들에게 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.03,0:46:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So a wise prayer is to pray to be able to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.46,0:47:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,그래서 현명한 기도는 이해할 수 있도록 해달라고 기도하는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.90,0:47:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then your guiding angels get your willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.19,0:47:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and see to it that you come into the presence of a teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.19,0:47:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who will explain what you need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.69,0:47:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and willing to know and able to grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.57,0:47:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇게 기도하게 되면 당신의 안내를
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.50,0:47:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,당신의 안내를 알 수 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.59,0:47:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,당신의 안내 천사가 당신이
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.15,0:47:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,그것을 진실을 이해할 수 있고
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.11,0:47:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,듣고 이해할 수 있도록 전달해 줄 수 있는
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.86,0:47:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,스승의 현존에 있게끔 해줍니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.13,0:47:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so the Buddha was a great teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.48,0:47:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke from wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.46,0:47:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,부처는 지혜로부터 지혜의 말씀을 하신
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.92,0:47:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,훌륭한 스승이었습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.78,0:47:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, let those who can hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.15,0:47:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 이해할 수 있는 사람들에게
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.15,0:47:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 이해할 수 있는 사람들에게
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.19,0:47:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 듣도록 들어라.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.86,0:47:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,라고 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.76,0:48:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let those who can hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.28,0:48:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.42,0:48:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,들을 수 있는 자만이 들어라.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.09,0:48:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.76,0:48:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,호케스 밥스님이 좋아하시는 겁니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.19,0:48:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.59,0:48:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's non-controlling, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.07,0:48:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's acknowledging that your capacity to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.84,0:48:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,is considerably your own karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.78,0:48:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not be able to hear, and it's not your fault
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.15,0:48:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because at this point you cannot hear yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.94,0:48:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.98,0:48:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 그러한 것은 통제하는 것이 아니니까요.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.07,0:48:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 그러한 것은 통제하는 것이 아니니까요.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.82,0:48:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,부처님께서는 당신이 들을 수 있는 능력은
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.78,0:48:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,당신의 카르마적인 어떤 자산이라는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.53,0:48:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,인정하셨습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.69,0:48:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.59,0:48:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, truth then tries to inspire and lead people
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.46,0:48:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to the truth or to the conditions that allow you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.01,0:48:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.94,0:48:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why humility is constantly stressed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.46,0:48:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in all spiritual teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.86,0:48:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.94,0:48:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.94,0:48:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.44,0:48:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은, uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.92,0:49:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 당신에게, 당신이 그것을 이해할 수 있는 조건들을
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.34,0:49:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,허락해 주기 때문에, 그래서 겸손함이라는 것이
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.84,0:49:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,계속해서 강조되는 이유입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.40,0:49:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth does not seek to control others.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.53,0:49:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 다른 이들을 통제하려 하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.84,0:49:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't want to have to convince others or force others.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.05,0:49:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 다른 사람을 확신시키려고 하지도 않고
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.51,0:49:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 다른 사람을 확신시키려고 하지도 않고
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.53,0:49:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,강제하지도 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.53,0:49:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You will go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.59,0:49:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, there are no issues or positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.15,0:49:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,어떤 문제도 없고 위치성도 있지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.11,0:49:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.03,0:49:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,신은 도움을 필요로 하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.19,0:49:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,People, I think, they're helping God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.94,0:50:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I will, if you don't believe the way I believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.71,0:50:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll cut your head off.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.21,0:50:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And he thinks that way you're helping God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.78,0:50:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to become humble and realize
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.32,0:50:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.32,0:50:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에 우리는 신이 우리의 도움을 필요로 하지 않는다는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.94,0:50:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,느끼고 겸손해져야 합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.78,0:50:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,God's made it this far without your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.96,0:50:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,신은 당신의 도움 없이도 이렇게 훌륭하십니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.84,0:50:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so the more sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.59,0:50:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we become, we become aware that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.76,0:50:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity is like an infinite source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.46,0:50:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,infinitely powerful source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.61,0:50:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that within that field,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.09,0:51:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you are free to move about or come or go.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.46,0:51:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.71,0:51:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,우리가 점점 더 진보함에 따라서 우리는 신성이라고 하는 것이
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.88,0:51:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,에너지의 무한한 근원이라는 것을 이해하고
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.38,0:51:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,그 안에서 우리는 자유롭게 움직일 수 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.17,0:51:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so that which all spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.51,0:51:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite spiritual truth is beyond proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.34,0:51:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,모든 영적인 진실은 증명을 넘어서 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.61,0:51:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is provable is within the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.17,0:51:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.86,0:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,증명할 수 있는 것은 선형적인 뉴톤적 영역에 속하는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.82,0:51:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that which is provable,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.67,0:51:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is obviously not divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.73,0:51:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에 분명히 증명할 수 있는 것은 신성한 것이 아닙니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.03,0:51:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can prove the infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.44,0:52:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,무한을 증명할 수 있는 방법은 존재하지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.13,0:52:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of the journals having to do with religion and things
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.30,0:52:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.53,0:52:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all about theology and God and all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.48,0:52:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you calibrate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.48,0:52:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they're like in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.32,0:52:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So what they're talking about is not the reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.84,0:52:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but intellectualizations about the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.82,0:52:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,종교나 그러한 신학에 관한 그러한 학술 잡지들은
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.15,0:52:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,측정을 해본다면 300대로 측정됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.30,0:52:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,이 사실이 말하는 것은 그들은 신성이라고 하는 것을
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.05,0:52:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,실상이 아닌 단지 주지화하고 있는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.19,0:52:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.57,0:52:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this one is...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.25,0:52:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the basics to know that is that life is not subject to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.17,0:53:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's the law of the preservation of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.23,0:53:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.03,0:53:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.21,0:53:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Matter cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.46,0:53:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.69,0:53:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,알아야 하실 아주 기본적인 것은 생명이 파괴될 수 없다는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.09,0:53:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,진량 보존의 법칙과 에너지 법칙,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.73,0:53:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,보존의 법칙이 있듯이 에너지가 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있듯이 생명도 그러합니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.50,0:53:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.96,0:53:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, more recently discovered is the third principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.98,0:53:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, the truth cannot be, life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.92,0:53:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.61,0:53:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.03,0:53:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So matter cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.96,0:53:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.51,0:53:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the third great discovery is that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.48,0:53:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.21,0:54:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Material can only change form from one form to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.42,0:54:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy can only change from one form to another,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.78,0:54:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot destroy energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.61,0:54:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,생명이...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.25,0:54:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.96,0:54:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, I forgot about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.90,0:54:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,에너지가 소멸될 수 없고, 진량이, 물질이 소멸될 수 없듯이,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.07,0:54:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째 위대한 발견은 생명도 파괴될 수 없다는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.80,0:54:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're all familiar with the basic concept that matter cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.86,0:54:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.19,0:54:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,우리는 모두 물질이 파괴될 수 없고, 단지 형태만을 바꿀 수 있다는 것을 잘 알고 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.44,0:54:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And energy cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.96,0:54:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.07,0:55:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,에너지도 파괴될 수 없고, 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.15,0:55:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, a third discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.98,0:55:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.01,0:55:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째 발견입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.90,0:55:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The third discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.19,0:55:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the third discovery again?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.51,0:55:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.71,0:55:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.44,0:55:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,세 번째 발견은 생명도 파괴될 수 없고, 단지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있을 뿐입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.13,0:55:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.86,0:55:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, known before was that matter and energy cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.26,0:55:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But nowhere have I ever read that life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.90,0:55:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,이전에 에너지와 물질이,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.76,0:55:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,에너지와 물질이,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.86,0:55:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,파괴될 수 없다는 것은 모두 알고 있었지만,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.67,0:55:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,누구도 생명이 파괴될 수 없고, 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있다는 것은 들어본 적이 없을 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.88,0:55:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Like matter and energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.01,0:55:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,life can only change form, but you cannot destroy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.61,0:55:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.94,0:56:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,에너지와 물질과 마찬가지로 생명은 파괴될 수 없고, 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.34,0:56:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.11,0:56:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.80,0:56:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.44,0:56:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing that can happen if they chop off your head is that you leave your physical body and there you are in your etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.46,0:56:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에, 누군가 당신의 머리를 잘라낸다면, 육체성은 사라지지만, 당신은 이제 이 에테르체에 있게 됩니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.30,0:56:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've been in my physical body and thought that's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.01,0:56:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,저는 육체 없이 에테르체에 있었습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.76,0:56:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,있어본 적이 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.63,0:56:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I've been out of my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.38,0:56:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,저는 육체를 벗어난 적도 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.84,0:56:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body was over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.59,0:56:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,육체는 저기에 있었고.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.84,0:56:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And consciousness says, this is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.88,0:56:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,의식은, 이게 나다 라고 말했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.36,0:56:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the body is there and me is here. How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.17,0:56:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,육체는 저기 있고, 저는 여기 있고. 이것이 어떻게 가능할까요?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.28,0:57:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you also have an etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.28,0:57:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,왜냐하면 당신은 또한 에테르체도 가지고 있기 때문입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.53,0:57:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit, the soul, that which leaves the body at the point of death, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.53,0:57:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,영과 영혼은 육신이 죽을 때 몸을 떠납니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.53,0:57:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a third great teaching is that life cannot be destroyed, it can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.21,0:57:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,그러므로 세 번째 위대한 가르침은, 생명은 파괴될 수 없고 오로지 형상만을 바꿀 수 있다는 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.21,0:57:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true at the level of the absolute resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.84,0:57:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That is true at the level of the absolute, life cannot be destroyed, it can only change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.63,0:57:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.15,0:57:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,좋은 소식 아닌가요?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.19,0:57:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like being a human being, you can come back. Hop, hop, hop, bunny, bunny. Hop, hop, bunny, bunny.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.36,0:57:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,사람이 되기 싫으면 말로 태어나실 수도 있습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.36,0:58:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,새로 태어나실 수도 있고요.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.42,0:58:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it would be great to be an eagle. Go up a mile in the sky, and ten miles away you can spot a mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.28,0:58:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that must be something.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.28,0:58:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,독수리가 된다는 것은 굉장히 멋질 거라고 생각했습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.28,0:58:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,한 천 미터도 넘게 올라가서 쥐를 볼 수 있는 능력을 갖는다.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.28,0:58:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even need glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.28,0:58:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,안경도 필요 없습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.07,0:58:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The eagle, miles away, can spot a mouse from over a thousand feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.07,0:58:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see. I think that's the last of the slides, and then we're going to go on to more interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.82,0:58:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what they are, but that's what they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.82,0:58:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the end of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.19,0:58:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.07,0:58:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.57,0:59:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One sees the intrinsic beauty of that which is beyond appearance and form.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.57,0:59:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in a moment of mystical revelation, the overwhelming beauty of what exists, you're knocked out by the beauty, beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.57,0:59:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,그렇기 때문에
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.76,0:59:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,압도적인 드러남의 상태에서 모든 것에 내지 않은 본질적인 아름다움이 당신을 쓰러트려 버립니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.76,0:59:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth does not do anything. It just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.19,0:59:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And its influence is as a consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.63,0:59:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 어떤 것도 하지 않으며, 모든 것을 그저 그것의 존재로서 영향을 미칩니다. 모든 것에.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.63,0:59:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.63,0:59:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And truth is not emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.63,0:59:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionality is based on perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.44,0:59:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 감정적이지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.44,0:59:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,감정성이라는 것은 지각에 근거한 것입니다.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.96,1:00:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is sought, is found through freedom, rather than rules and restrictions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.96,1:00:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,진실은 자유를 통해서 따르게 되며, 따르게 되지, 룰이나 이런 것으로 인해서 지켜지지 않습니다.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.21,1:00:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And true spiritual teachers are respected,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.78,1:00:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but they reject personal adulation or specialness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.84,1:00:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,진정한 스승은 존경되기는 하나, 개인적인 찬양은 거절합니다.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.84,1:00:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The recognition of truth is natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.84,1:00:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's devoid of induced, altered states of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.84,1:00:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,various manipulating energies up and down the spine,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.84,1:00:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and magical breathing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.00,1:00:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.59,1:00:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.78,1:01:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrates over 190, 195.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.34,1:01:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of those students all over the planet doing,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.01,1:01:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.01,1:01:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dumber than when you started it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.23,1:01:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,이 호흡법은 195로 측정되며, 이걸 하게 되면 당신이 시작하기 전보다 더 어리석게 되죠.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.19,1:01:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, alright, we're almost done.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.19,1:01:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wise then,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.61,1:01:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to really check out the integrity of a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.61,1:01:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a teaching, a method,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.61,1:01:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that it's called yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.61,1:01:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.96,1:01:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you a yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.96,1:01:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Try this yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.17,1:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Try that yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.17,1:01:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Try this yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.40,1:01:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that it's called a yoga,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.32,1:01:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a mystical, magical,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.32,1:02:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,better than butter is yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.76,1:02:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga spread.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.73,1:02:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga talks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.38,1:02:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga socks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.40,1:02:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga shoes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.73,1:02:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoga flowers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.15,1:02:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll do all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.15,1:02:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.07,1:02:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.63,1:02:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.63,1:02:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for being our translator.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.63,1:03:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell the people what are we going to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.00,1:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what we're going to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.00,1:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a 15-minute break here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.00,1:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyone who has a question,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.00,1:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if they will please line up on this side.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.00,1:03:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.00,1:03:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The auditorium.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.00,1:03:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who needs book signing,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.00,1:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we did sign a lot of the books.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.00,1:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you want something signed,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.00,1:03:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,take it to this side of the auditorium.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.00,1:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll resume in about 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.00,1:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a little bit over,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.00,1:03:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so we'll probably run over a little bit in the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.00,1:03:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're a little bit over.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.00,1:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this lady over here that's in the Korean costume,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.00,1:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.00,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is typical of the Korean dress.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.00,1:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.00,1:03:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted all of you to take a look.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.00,1:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a good look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.00,1:03:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.84,1:03:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to see your dress.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.84,1:03:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the people here in the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.84,1:03:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't seen the traditional Korean.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.84,1:03:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.84,1:03:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your playing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.84,1:03:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.84,1:03:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.21,1:04:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.21,1:04:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.21,1:04:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll resume in about 15 minutes then.
